	details = <
		["nb"] = <
			language = <[ISO_639-1::nb]>
			purpose = <"*To record formal decisions about emergency care and treatment, including overall goals of care and guidance about future, critical, medical interventions that may save or prolong the life of an individual. (en)">
			use = <"*Use to record formal decisions about the intent for future emergency care and treatment, as asserted by an authorised clinician. These decisions include overall goals of care and guidance regarding cardiopulmonary resuscitation and other critical medical interventions that may save or prolong the life of an individual.

It is recommended that the decisions about emergency care and treatment are made after careful consideration of the preferences asserted by the individual or documented in their 'Advance Care Directive', or similar.

The proposed DV_CODED_TEXT value set for the 'Intervention' data element is not intended to be exhaustive but to include many of the common life-saving treatments. The alternate choice of the DV_TEXT option can be used to add a local value set or bind to an external value set within a template.

It is assumed that any treatments intended to provide symptom relief and comfort to the individual are always administered as clinically appropriate. (en)">
			keywords = <"*DNR (en)", "*DNAR (en)", "*DNACPR (en)", "*NFR (en)", "*resuscitation (en)", "*resuscitate (en)", "*EoL (en)", "*end of life (en)", "*directive (en)", "*preference (en)", "*goal (en)", "*care (en)", "*intervention (en)">
			misuse = <"*Not to be used to record an 'Advance care directive' or other personal preferences - use EVALUATION.advance_care_directive for this purpose.(en)">
		>
		["en"] = <
			language = <[ISO_639-1::en]>
			purpose = <"To record formal decisions about emergency care and treatment, including overall goals of care and guidance about future, critical, medical interventions that may save or prolong the life of an individual.">
			use = <"Use to record formal decisions about the intent for future emergency care and treatment, as asserted by an authorised clinician. These decisions include overall goals of care and guidance regarding cardiopulmonary resuscitation and other critical medical interventions that may save or prolong the life of an individual.

It is recommended that the decisions about emergency care and treatment are made after careful consideration of the preferences asserted by the individual or documented in their 'Advance Care Directive', or similar.

The proposed DV_CODED_TEXT value set for the 'Intervention' data element is not intended to be exhaustive but to include many of the common life-saving treatments. The alternate choice of the DV_TEXT option can be used to add a local value set or bind to an external value set within a template.

It is assumed that any treatments intended to provide symptom relief and comfort to the individual are always administered as clinically appropriate.">
